name: TresPass
description:
When the color breaks 
We see our holds hovering above 
We beg the truth is that we- 
-Carbon mankind-are merely passing
Value on in some other way 
We wouldn't want for ourselves
To the incomprehensible sediment layers overhead  
As a driven stampede unable to break the shackles of need
Perhaps we are trespassing 
By design.

Work derived from original photography from IG:@Street_Art_Community in New York City an East River view, a World Trade Center view including partial street art from Todd Gray and others. CC Attribution for the model the ship was built in to 'MJ lee'. Music: Charon by Yehezkel Raz (reversed). Poem by 2quantum@pm.me. One version will be permanently applied to a dystopian game coming 2022.
